        "subject": "LU-11030 fld: initialize index and req variables",
        "message": "LU-11030 fld: initialize index and req variables\n\nInitialize `index` and `req` in fld_update_from_controller()\nto prevent use of uninitialized variables. The `req` pointer\ncould be dereferenced in the cleanup path if fld_client_rpc()\nreturns early without setting *reqp.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Sohei Koyama <skoyama@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: I59c805c8d1c273d24f22849d934d64198ee5cfe4\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63837\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\n"
